com.symantec.dlpx.flexresponse

Class DefaultPluginMetadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.symantec.dlpx.flexresponse.DefaultPluginMetadata
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PluginMetadata

    public final class DefaultPluginMetadata
extends java.lang.Object
implements PluginMetadata
    This class gives you a default implementation of plugin metadata. You can use this when you return metadata for your plugin in the Plugin.getMetadata() method. It is particularly recommended that you use this given that PluginMetadata currently is not used. This class follows the "best practice" of returning null for the display name and identifier, which requires that the plugin properties file provide this information. This is recommended because it documents this information in the properties file rather than "hiding" it in your plugin source code.

        Create a new instance of DefaultPluginMetadata
        Parameters:
        vendor - the vendor providing the plugin.
        version - the version of the plugin.
        attributes - any attributes you would like to provide about this plugin. If you have no attributes, do not use null. Instead, provide an empty list, e.g. using Collections.EMPTY_MAP.
